functions.label: getBaselineAndDeviationRates
description:
Calculates the baseline and deviation rates for log rate analysis based on the specified analysis type.

This function computes the rates by dividing the document count (docCount) and background count (bgCount)
by the number of buckets allocated for baseline and deviation periods, respectively. The calculation
method varies depending on whether the analysis type is a "spike" or a "dip". For a "spike", the baseline
rate is derived from the background count and the deviation rate from the document count. For a "dip",
the roles are reversed.
signature: , baselineBuckets: number, deviationBuckets: number, docCount: number, bgCount: number) => { baselineBucketRate: number; deviationBucketRate: number; }

children.label: analysisType
description: The type of analysis to perform, can be either "spike" or "dip".

children.label: baselineBuckets
description: The number of buckets into which the baseline period is divided.

children.label: deviationBuckets
description: The number of buckets into which the deviation period is divided.

children.label: docCount
description: The total document count observed in the deviation period.

children.label: bgCount
description: The total background count observed in the baseline period.

returnComment: An object containing the calculated baseline and deviation bucket rates.

functions.label: getExtendedChangePoint
description: Calculates and returns an extended change point range based on the specified change point timestamp.
signature: (buckets: Record<string, number>, changePointTs: number) => { startTs: number; endTs: number; }

children.label: buckets
description:
- An object where keys are bucket timestamps as strings
  and values are numeric values associated with each bucket.

children.label: changePointTs
description:
- The timestamp of the change point as a number. This timestamp must
  be one of the keys in the `buckets` object.

returnComment: An object containing two properties: `startTs` and `endTs`.

functions.label: getLogRateChange
description:
Calculates the change in log rate between two time periods and generates a descriptive message.
It return the factor as a number as well as a human readable message.
signature: , baselineBucketRate: number, deviationBucketRate: number) => { message: string; factor?: number | undefined; }

children.label: analysisType
description: The type of log rate analysis (spike or dip).

children.label: baselineBucketRate
description: The log rate (document count per unit time) during the baseline period.

children.label: deviationBucketRate
description: The log rate (document count per unit time) during the deviation period.

returnComment: An object containing the message describing the rate change and the factor of change if applicable.

children.label: timeRangeLatest

children.label: interval

returnComment: Array of timestamps spaced by the specified interval within the given range.

functions.label: getSwappedWindowParameters
description: Swaps the baseline and deviation window parameters. To be used when we identify the type of analysis to be 'dip'.

children.label: windowParameters
description: An object containing the window parameters for baseline and deviation periods.

returnComment: A new `WindowParameters` object with the baseline and deviation parameters swapped.

functions.label: getWindowParameters
description:
Given a point in time (e.g. where a user clicks), use simple heuristics to compute:

1. The time window around the click to evaluate for changes
2. The historical time window prior to the click to use as a baseline.

The philosophy here is that charts are displayed with different granularities according to their
overall time window. We select the log deviation and historical time windows inline with the
overall time window.

The algorithm for doing this is based on the typical granularities that exist in machine data.
signature: (clickTime: number, minTime: number, maxTime: number, clickTimeUpper?: number | undefined, windowGapOverride?: number | undefined) =>

children.label: clickTime
description: timestamp of the clicked log rate deviation.

children.label: minTime
description: minimum timestamp of the time window to be analysed

children.label: maxTime
description: maximum timestamp of the time window to be analysed

children.label: clickTimeUpper
description:
optional timestamp to treat clicktime and clickTimeUpper
as a time range instead of point in time

children.label: windowGapOverride
description: optional override for the baseline/deviation gap

functions.label: getWindowParametersForTrigger
description:
Calculates window parameters, adjusting the window based on a
change point and interval. If a change point is specified and falls within
the startRange, the window is adjusted around the change point. Otherwise,
the window is determined by the startRange and interval.
signature: , interval: number, timeRangeEarliest: number, timeRangeLatest: number, changePoint:

children.label: startRange
description:
The start timestamp or window parameters. If a number,
it's the start timestamp; if an object, it's assumed to be
window parameters and is returned directly.

children.label: interval
description:
Interval in milliseconds for extending the window or
adjusting the start range.

children.label: timeRangeEarliest
description: Earliest timestamp in milliseconds in the time range.

children.label: timeRangeLatest
description: Latest timestamp in milliseconds in the time range.

children.label: changePoint
description:
Optional change point with `startTs` and `endTs`
properties. Adjusts window parameters if within `startRange`.
